---
// "Built by a passholder" teaser (website_plan §1b #8) — the homepage gets
// this short version; /about carries the full story. Light section so it
// reads as a breather between the dark SocialProof and the FAQ.
---
<section id="founder" class="section founder">
  <div class="container founder__inner">
    <p class="kicker">Built by a passholder</p>
    <h2 class="display founder__title">Made in Orlando, by one of you.</h2>
    <p class="founder__body">
      Lanyard is independent. No park built it, no park sponsors it, and
      that's the point: the tool that tracks every operator's passes has to
      answer only to the passholder holding them.
    </p>
    <a class="founder__link" href="/about">Read the story →</a>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .founder { background: var(--off-white); color: var(--ink); }
  .founder__inner { text-align: center; max-width: 38rem; margin-inline: auto; }
  .founder .kicker { color: var(--green-primary); }
  .founder__title { font-size: var(--fs-h2); margin: 0.6rem auto 0; }
  .founder__body {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: var(--fs-lead);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 1.2rem auto 0;
    max-width: 46ch;
  }
  .founder__link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 1.4rem;
    color: var(--green-primary);
    font-weight: 700;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .founder__link:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
</style>
